1
00:00:32,281 --> 00:00:36,953
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

2
00:00:41,123 --> 00:00:42,416
Isn't the ice cream so sweet?

3
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:44,460
It's my favorite.

4
00:00:45,169 --> 00:00:47,338
Yeah, even the ice cream's sweet.

5
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:52,885
I still can't believe it.

6
00:00:53,344 --> 00:00:56,806
I like you, and you like me back.

7
00:00:57,682 --> 00:00:59,350
What are the chances, really?

8
00:01:00,393 --> 00:01:02,562
I know, right? It's so cool.

9
00:01:04,355 --> 00:01:05,356
I'll...

10
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:08,359
remember this day for a long time.

11
00:01:10,611 --> 00:01:15,408
If we ever get disappointed in
or mad at each other

12
00:01:15,783 --> 00:01:17,243
let's remind ourselves of today.

13
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:22,081
Let's think about the astronomical odds
we beat to get here and get through it.

14
00:01:23,124 --> 00:01:24,125
Okay.

15
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:27,837
But I'll be so good to you
that you won't even have to think that.

16
00:01:35,052 --> 00:01:38,639
Do you want to walk more
until we finish this?

17
00:01:39,807 --> 00:01:41,267
Sounds good.

18
00:01:47,940 --> 00:01:49,108
You should go home now.

19
00:01:49,191 --> 00:01:51,277
We're going to stay out all night
at this rate.

20
00:01:52,653 --> 00:01:54,530
It already feels
like it's getting brighter.

21
00:01:54,989 --> 00:01:56,115
You think so?

22
00:01:56,616 --> 00:01:59,869
Everything goes by so quickly
when I'm with you.

23
00:02:00,745 --> 00:02:03,122
So, what are you doing tomorrow?

24
00:02:03,497 --> 00:02:04,498
Tomorrow?

25
00:02:05,249 --> 00:02:06,292
Nothing much.

26
00:02:06,375 --> 00:02:09,420
I usually do nothing
and recharge on Sundays.

27
00:02:09,837 --> 00:02:11,589
Do you want to do nothing with me

28
00:02:12,006 --> 00:02:13,841
tomorrow at my house?

29
00:02:13,924 --> 00:02:16,135
At your house?

30
00:02:16,218 --> 00:02:17,261
Yeah.

31
00:02:19,013 --> 00:02:22,516
Sure, I'll come to your place
around lunch tomorrow.

32
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,893
Maybe 1 p.m.?

33
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:25,936
Come at noon. I'll cook for you.

34
00:02:26,020 --> 00:02:27,563
I can't wait!

35
00:02:27,647 --> 00:02:29,357
Don't set your expectations too high.

36
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:31,317
Bye, then.

37
00:02:48,167 --> 00:02:49,460
See you tomorrow. No.

38
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:51,337
See you real soon.

39
00:02:59,011 --> 00:03:00,471
I can't believe it.

40
00:03:03,432 --> 00:03:09,605
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE
EPISODE 9

41
00:03:17,196 --> 00:03:18,447
That night

42
00:03:18,739 --> 00:03:21,992
I couldn't stop thinking
about how cruel love can be.

43
00:03:26,205 --> 00:03:28,791
Could you give this to her for me?

44
00:03:28,874 --> 00:03:31,419
She lives here. Her name is Lee Ui-yeong.

45
00:03:31,502 --> 00:03:33,212
I remember you from last time.

46
00:03:33,295 --> 00:03:35,798
Why don't you give it to her yourself?

47
00:03:36,757 --> 00:03:38,050
Please help me.

48
00:03:38,217 --> 00:03:39,468
Oh, sure.

49
00:03:39,552 --> 00:03:42,513
Love makes us burn with passion

50
00:03:43,180 --> 00:03:44,974
only to lead us to a dead end.

51
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:48,853
It teaches us
the joy of being with someone else

52
00:03:49,812 --> 00:03:53,023
only to have every little thing
make us anxious

53
00:03:53,107 --> 00:03:54,859
that it won't last.

54
00:03:56,444 --> 00:03:58,863
I really wanted to do well this time.

55
00:03:58,946 --> 00:04:00,072
TIME'S UP

56
00:04:01,615 --> 00:04:02,742
Maybe that's why

57
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:07,121
it felt so miraculous
that we felt the same way

58
00:04:07,705 --> 00:04:11,000
at the same time.

59
00:04:12,376 --> 00:04:14,462
Love will always be cruel

60
00:04:16,046 --> 00:04:18,632
but I know I'm stronger.

61
00:04:20,092 --> 00:04:21,719
I'll be good to her.

62
00:04:32,104 --> 00:04:36,233
It's better to stick to a recipe
I know will work.

63
00:04:37,651 --> 00:04:39,403
Oh, it's Tae-seop!

64
00:04:39,487 --> 00:04:40,529
Huh?

65
00:04:40,613 --> 00:04:42,823
- Hi, Mother.
- Hey, Tae-seop!

66
00:04:42,907 --> 00:04:44,784
I'm trying to make tteokbokki at home.

67
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,660
What's your recipe for the sauce?

68
00:04:46,744 --> 00:04:47,870
Tteokbokki?

69
00:04:48,037 --> 00:04:49,914
Oh, is Sua coming over?

70
00:04:49,997 --> 00:04:51,582
You want the milder version, then?

71
00:04:51,665 --> 00:04:54,543
No, the spicy version for adults.

72
00:04:55,002 --> 00:04:56,045
For adults...

73
00:04:56,670 --> 00:04:58,672
Oh! Are you...

74
00:04:59,006 --> 00:05:01,717
cooking for that lady?

75
00:05:01,801 --> 00:05:03,135
Yeah.

76
00:05:03,969 --> 00:05:05,763
We're dating now.

77
00:05:07,348 --> 00:05:10,226
They're dating now!

78
00:05:10,351 --> 00:05:13,562
Okay, let me give you the spiciest recipe!

79
00:05:13,646 --> 00:05:17,066
You know how I made your dad fall for me
with my cooking!

80
00:05:17,149 --> 00:05:18,984
I knew I couldn't promise you

81
00:05:19,068 --> 00:05:21,237
a queen's life without chores
after I had your food.

82
00:05:21,987 --> 00:05:24,865
Well, I hope it works for me, too.

83
00:05:25,074 --> 00:05:26,742
Of course!

84
00:05:26,826 --> 00:05:28,035
Start taking notes.

85
00:05:28,118 --> 00:05:31,038
Gochujang, chili powder, sugar, and MSG.

86
00:05:31,121 --> 00:05:33,833
Don't forget minced garlic and scallions.

87
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:35,000
Oh, and canola oil!

88
00:05:35,084 --> 00:05:36,252
Canola oil?

89
00:05:36,335 --> 00:05:38,671
Oh, yeah, that's the secret
of every tteokbokki master.

90
00:05:38,754 --> 00:05:41,507
That brings all the flavors together.

91
00:05:43,008 --> 00:05:44,802
How much do I add of each thing?

92
00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:49,640
Yeah, anything's possible.

93
00:05:52,977 --> 00:05:54,687
I need matching lingerie.

94
00:05:54,770 --> 00:05:56,397
What would be the best?

95
00:05:57,481 --> 00:05:58,482
Mom!

96
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:02,236
Mom! Have you seen my light blue blouse?

97
00:06:03,487 --> 00:06:04,655
Yeah, that!

98
00:06:05,573 --> 00:06:07,992
Oh, gosh! What was that about? My hair!

99
00:06:08,826 --> 00:06:10,870
Make me some ramyeon. With an egg.

100
00:06:10,953 --> 00:06:11,996
- Now?
- Yeah.

101
00:06:12,079 --> 00:06:13,372
I'm heading out for lunch.

102
00:06:13,455 --> 00:06:14,915
I'll heat the water for you.

103
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:16,625
Next time, okay? Sorry, and thanks.

104
00:06:18,711 --> 00:06:21,380
She looks like a kid
who's about to go on a field trip.

105
00:06:23,841 --> 00:06:25,092
Is she seeing someone?

106
00:06:27,386 --> 00:06:29,096
- Excuse me!
- Hello.

107
00:06:29,179 --> 00:06:30,389
Yeah, that's you.

108
00:06:31,098 --> 00:06:33,851
The tall young guy left this with me
last night.

109
00:06:33,934 --> 00:06:35,603
It's yours, right?

110
00:06:36,478 --> 00:06:38,230
Oh, yeah, it is. Thank you.

111
00:06:38,314 --> 00:06:40,274
Make sure to let him know you got it.

112
00:06:40,357 --> 00:06:41,400
Okay.

113
00:06:51,368 --> 00:06:52,578
Hey, Ji-su.

114
00:06:52,661 --> 00:06:55,414
Thanks for returning the cardigan to me.

115
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:57,416
Did you get home safely last night?

116
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:06,759
Thanks for the cardigan.

117
00:07:44,004 --> 00:07:45,547
- Ta-da. Congratulations
- Hm?

118
00:07:46,131 --> 00:07:47,549
you finally have a girlfriend.

119
00:07:48,300 --> 00:07:50,427
Thanks, I'll take good care of them.

120
00:07:58,477 --> 00:07:59,603
It smells amazing.

121
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:01,188
I can't wait!

122
00:08:05,109 --> 00:08:08,112
Some scallions and eomuk.

123
00:08:09,571 --> 00:08:11,490
That's how you make your tteokbokki.

124
00:08:11,740 --> 00:08:14,660
Every household has a different style.

125
00:08:14,743 --> 00:08:16,620
How does your family cook it?

126
00:08:16,704 --> 00:08:18,080
My family?

127
00:08:18,706 --> 00:08:20,624
Our style is not having a style.

128
00:08:21,166 --> 00:08:22,167
Hmm?

129
00:08:22,793 --> 00:08:26,171
My mom was always so busy,
we just bought it from different shops.

130
00:08:26,422 --> 00:08:28,966
So, we don't have a go-to recipe
for kimchi jjigae, either.

131
00:08:29,049 --> 00:08:30,134
I see.

132
00:08:30,259 --> 00:08:32,136
Oh! Can you add all the eomuk?

133
00:08:32,219 --> 00:08:33,262
You want more?

134
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:36,765
- You like eomuk.
- This looks amazing!

135
00:08:36,974 --> 00:08:38,058
Here.

136
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:39,977
- Try some.
- Okay.

137
00:08:40,728 --> 00:08:41,895
I'll start with the tteok.

138
00:08:46,942 --> 00:08:47,943
How is it?

139
00:08:48,944 --> 00:08:50,696
- It's amazing!
- Is it?

140
00:08:51,947 --> 00:08:52,990
I'm so glad.

141
00:08:54,950 --> 00:08:56,243
I'll try the eomuk now.

142
00:09:12,384 --> 00:09:15,095
Gosh, you were so pale

143
00:09:15,262 --> 00:09:16,764
and so tiny!

144
00:09:16,847 --> 00:09:19,767
How did such a tiny person grow so big?

145
00:09:20,142 --> 00:09:22,978
I hit a growth spurt in 11th grade.

146
00:09:23,062 --> 00:09:24,188
I see.

147
00:09:24,271 --> 00:09:25,856
I see your parents!

148
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:33,906
How come you don't have any photos
from when you were in school?

149
00:09:34,323 --> 00:09:37,284
Oh, that was when my father's company
went bankrupt

150
00:09:37,367 --> 00:09:40,662
and he opened the restaurant with Mom.

151
00:09:40,746 --> 00:09:41,747
I see.

152
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:46,085
Was that the time
you didn't have a dining table at home?

153
00:09:46,168 --> 00:09:47,753
Yeah.

154
00:09:51,173 --> 00:09:52,174
Here.

155
00:09:52,257 --> 00:09:54,510
My dad's really clever.

156
00:09:54,802 --> 00:09:56,720
It was a stressful time for everyone

157
00:09:56,804 --> 00:09:59,515
so he thought it'd be a great idea
to sell spicy chicken feet

158
00:09:59,598 --> 00:10:01,391
in an area
full of stressed office workers.

159
00:10:02,017 --> 00:10:03,727
He entirely relied on my mom's cooking.

160
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:04,812
I see.

161
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:07,439
It must've been tough to sell chicken feet

162
00:10:07,523 --> 00:10:10,567
at their very first restaurant.

163
00:10:10,651 --> 00:10:11,944
Whenever they got tired

164
00:10:12,027 --> 00:10:15,239
they leaned on each other to stay strong.

165
00:10:17,282 --> 00:10:18,700
I see

166
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:22,037
why you think
getting married is so natural.

167
00:10:24,373 --> 00:10:27,543
- This is my first time telling you this.
- Yeah?

168
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:31,713
My parents separated years ago.

169
00:10:32,631 --> 00:10:34,925
I see.

170
00:10:35,134 --> 00:10:38,053
It's their personalities.
They're too different.

171
00:10:39,471 --> 00:10:41,849
Maybe that's why

172
00:10:41,932 --> 00:10:45,060
but thinking about getting married seems
like none of my business.

173
00:10:45,727 --> 00:10:48,647
And it also makes dating harder for me.

174
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:53,026
It's like tteokbokki and kimchi jjigae.
I don't know what to look for.

175
00:10:55,863 --> 00:10:57,447
But that's okay.

176
00:10:57,531 --> 00:10:59,575
Do what you did earlier.

177
00:10:59,658 --> 00:11:02,369
You can add extra eomuk
and whatever you like.

178
00:11:03,287 --> 00:11:05,831
Let's build a relationship
the way we want.

179
00:11:06,415 --> 00:11:07,457
Sounds good.

180
00:11:08,041 --> 00:11:09,626
Oh, then...

181
00:11:10,419 --> 00:11:12,129
- Since we're dating now...
- Yeah?

182
00:11:14,256 --> 00:11:15,299
This.

183
00:11:15,924 --> 00:11:17,259
Can you give this to me?

184
00:11:17,342 --> 00:11:20,304
I don't know. I don't have many photos
where I look that cute.

185
00:11:20,387 --> 00:11:21,388
What?

186
00:11:22,723 --> 00:11:24,391
All of these photos are so cute!

187
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:27,227
Okay, bring a cute baby photo of you
next time.

188
00:11:27,311 --> 00:11:28,353
Let's exchange them.

189
00:11:28,729 --> 00:11:30,772
- Does it have to be just as cute?
- Of course.

190
00:11:30,856 --> 00:11:31,940
Not sure if I have any.

191
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:33,984
It won't be easy to find one.

192
00:11:35,194 --> 00:11:36,236
Oh?

193
00:11:36,486 --> 00:11:37,863
- Just a sec.
- Okay.

194
00:11:38,530 --> 00:11:40,365
Hello? Hey, I'm...

195
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:43,243
Ui-yeong!

196
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:45,621
What? Are you crying?

197
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:49,082
Can you come over to my place right now?

198
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:50,167
Right now?

199
00:11:54,546 --> 00:11:55,881
She meant it...

200
00:11:57,299 --> 00:11:59,009
She did not...

201
00:12:07,267 --> 00:12:09,811
Of course, she meant it!

202
00:12:09,978 --> 00:12:14,274
She got her fingers dirty
to rip the skin off for me...

203
00:12:21,907 --> 00:12:25,035
Man, you're an idiot!

204
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:28,288
You're so stupid!

205
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,127
You're such a chicken!

206
00:12:36,755 --> 00:12:37,756
Seung-jun!

207
00:12:38,382 --> 00:12:40,801
Yeah, that's me...

208
00:12:43,428 --> 00:12:44,888
How much did you drink?

209
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:46,014
Who are you?

210
00:12:46,181 --> 00:12:48,600
Oh, he's my boyfriend.

211
00:12:49,017 --> 00:12:50,894
I was with him when you called.

212
00:12:51,353 --> 00:12:53,647
- Say hi.
- Hello, I'm Song Tae-seop.

213
00:12:54,314 --> 00:12:56,775
- Say hi.
- Your boyfriend?

214
00:12:58,527 --> 00:12:59,861
I see...

215
00:13:00,654 --> 00:13:02,990
Hello, I'm Lim Seung-jun.

216
00:13:03,073 --> 00:13:04,533
- Nice to meet you.
- Yeah.

217
00:13:06,576 --> 00:13:09,496
My Ui-yeong finally has a boyfriend!

218
00:13:10,622 --> 00:13:12,958
Even she has a boyfriend...

219
00:13:17,045 --> 00:13:18,255
What about me?

220
00:13:20,257 --> 00:13:22,009
What about me?

221
00:13:24,219 --> 00:13:26,221
What are you doing? We're in public!

222
00:13:27,681 --> 00:13:29,474
Let's head out. Come on.

223
00:13:30,892 --> 00:13:32,060
I'll take him.

224
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:33,812
Please get up.

225
00:13:34,730 --> 00:13:36,189
Watch your step.

226
00:13:36,648 --> 00:13:38,317
I'm sorry!

227
00:13:38,483 --> 00:13:39,901
- Gosh.
- Be careful.

228
00:13:43,697 --> 00:13:44,740
Oh, goodness.

229
00:13:48,827 --> 00:13:50,037
That moron!

230
00:13:52,122 --> 00:13:53,123
You okay?

231
00:13:53,540 --> 00:13:55,584
How much did you drink?

232
00:13:56,585 --> 00:13:58,503
- You're ridiculous.
- Lie down first.

233
00:14:00,255 --> 00:14:01,256
Oh.

234
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:04,843
- Seriously.
- Take this.

235
00:14:08,305 --> 00:14:10,223
You're so nice for someone I just met.

236
00:14:10,724 --> 00:14:12,809
You know

237
00:14:13,477 --> 00:14:16,063
she needs a lot more care
than most people.

238
00:14:16,146 --> 00:14:20,192
She's a handful and then some.

239
00:14:20,275 --> 00:14:22,527
Yeah? That's cute.

240
00:14:23,111 --> 00:14:26,281
You know, you've been a handful, too.

241
00:14:26,365 --> 00:14:27,491
Sorry.

242
00:14:27,574 --> 00:14:30,202
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

243
00:14:30,410 --> 00:14:32,287
Why would you go this far?

244
00:14:32,371 --> 00:14:34,331
You were too busy talking about yourself.

245
00:14:35,415 --> 00:14:37,626
Were you even curious
about how I've been doing?

246
00:14:39,336 --> 00:14:41,505
We can't just assume

247
00:14:41,588 --> 00:14:44,383
people on dating apps are less serious
than those on blind dates.

248
00:14:44,466 --> 00:14:45,842
I can testify to that.

249
00:14:45,926 --> 00:14:48,095
You know how many weirdos go
on blind dates?

250
00:14:48,387 --> 00:14:50,305
You want me to remind you
of all my bad dates?

251
00:14:51,556 --> 00:14:54,351
So, how many blind dates have you been on?

252
00:14:54,518 --> 00:14:55,644
Just a few.

253
00:14:56,353 --> 00:14:58,980
Just tell her you were too close-minded

254
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:02,317
and apologize for saying
those on apps aren't serious.

255
00:15:02,692 --> 00:15:04,945
And explain that you were just scared!

256
00:15:05,028 --> 00:15:07,322
No, I can't.

257
00:15:07,531 --> 00:15:08,532
Why not?

258
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:11,451
She blocked me.

259
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:12,536
She blocked you?

260
00:15:12,661 --> 00:15:14,788
She didn't have to go that far.

261
00:15:14,913 --> 00:15:17,499
Hey, forget it.
You can't date someone like that.

262
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:20,168
She'd always make you anxious
if you dated her.

263
00:15:21,169 --> 00:15:22,546
Just get over her.

264
00:15:22,754 --> 00:15:23,839
Get over her, okay?

265
00:15:24,047 --> 00:15:25,173
You will, right?

266
00:15:25,924 --> 00:15:27,467
Answer me!

267
00:15:28,343 --> 00:15:29,428
Seriously.

268
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:32,180
Stop crying.

269
00:15:46,111 --> 00:15:47,529
Gosh, Seung-jun.

270
00:15:51,199 --> 00:15:53,994
Seung-jun played basketball
back in the day.

271
00:15:54,077 --> 00:15:57,372
- But he had to quit after a major injury.
- I see.

272
00:15:57,456 --> 00:16:00,083
So, it took a lot of hard work
to open that gym.

273
00:16:00,625 --> 00:16:03,170
He may seem strong on the outside

274
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:06,173
but I know his heart is so fragile.

275
00:16:06,256 --> 00:16:09,885
So, I just always wish
he'd take the easy way.

276
00:16:11,887 --> 00:16:15,932
But you'll be there for him
whenever he needs your help.

277
00:16:16,766 --> 00:16:17,893
Of course, that's my job.

278
00:16:19,227 --> 00:16:23,148
Sorry for dragging you
into this mess today.

279
00:16:24,024 --> 00:16:26,735
No, we ate tteokbokki and met your friend.

280
00:16:27,068 --> 00:16:30,489
It feels like we've gotten closer,
so I'm happy.

281
00:16:31,615 --> 00:16:32,741
I feel the same.

282
00:16:32,824 --> 00:16:36,119
Staying home was even better
than a staycation at a hotel.

283
00:16:36,828 --> 00:16:38,163
Do you like hotel staycations?

284
00:16:38,371 --> 00:16:41,833
Yeah, it's also a good chance
to learn about other hotels.

285
00:16:42,209 --> 00:16:44,503
- I see.
- Do you want to go sometime...

286
00:16:47,214 --> 00:16:48,673
Let's go together sometime.

287
00:16:49,090 --> 00:16:50,300
Whenever you want.

288
00:16:51,801 --> 00:16:52,844
Sounds good.

289
00:16:54,971 --> 00:16:57,390
How's work these days? Are you busy?

290
00:16:58,433 --> 00:17:00,977
I'll be busy for a while
because of the exhibition.

291
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:02,145
I see.

292
00:17:02,854 --> 00:17:04,940
When can we meet next...

293
00:17:05,023 --> 00:17:06,900
- Saturday.
- Saturday?

294
00:17:06,983 --> 00:17:09,236
That way, we can hang out late.

295
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:11,446
Oh, that's true.

296
00:17:13,990 --> 00:17:14,991
This is great.

297
00:17:20,163 --> 00:17:21,540
Have a good day.

298
00:17:21,998 --> 00:17:23,208
Happy Monday!

299
00:17:24,793 --> 00:17:28,630
HAVE A GOOD DAY. HAPPY MONDAY!

300
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:34,844
Why do we have to change the gift set
that has no problems?

301
00:17:34,970 --> 00:17:36,179
They really don't care

302
00:17:36,263 --> 00:17:38,765
about all the time we have to spend
to visit the producers!

303
00:17:39,516 --> 00:17:41,768
Do you think there was an issue
with the quality?

304
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:45,897
Not at all! We have such high standards!

305
00:17:46,106 --> 00:17:48,358
Whatever, Mr. Oh will take care of it.

306
00:17:48,441 --> 00:17:50,652
He hates extra work more than anyone.

307
00:17:54,781 --> 00:17:57,158
Why are you so tired?
We haven't even had the meeting.

308
00:17:58,118 --> 00:17:59,160
Sorry?

309
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:03,123
I have a lot going on in my life.

310
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:05,166
What happened? Oh!

311
00:18:07,377 --> 00:18:08,378
You want some?

312
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:11,131
Oh?

313
00:18:11,548 --> 00:18:14,301
Didn't I get this for you last time?

314
00:18:14,384 --> 00:18:17,596
Yeah, this kept me going
until the end of the day.

315
00:18:17,762 --> 00:18:19,723
- Take one and feel better.
-You're the best.

316
00:18:21,558 --> 00:18:23,143
What is it? Give me one.

317
00:18:23,351 --> 00:18:24,686
Here, have one.

318
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:26,896
I'm already so exhausted.

319
00:18:29,107 --> 00:18:31,776
- Let's go!
- Okay, let's go.

320
00:18:36,406 --> 00:18:37,407
Right on.

321
00:18:37,490 --> 00:18:39,326
Our gift set isn't competitive
in the market

322
00:18:39,409 --> 00:18:41,953
especially with online markets offering

323
00:18:42,037 --> 00:18:44,122
high-quality produce.

324
00:18:44,205 --> 00:18:46,833
That's why we want to make a new gift set.

325
00:18:46,916 --> 00:18:49,502
It feels like food trends come and go
even more quickly now.

326
00:18:49,711 --> 00:18:53,506
Even trending tteokbokki and pasta recipes

327
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:54,591
on social media platforms

328
00:18:54,674 --> 00:18:55,675
- change so often.
- Yeah.

329
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:59,679
But do we really need to keep up
with every trend?

330
00:18:59,763 --> 00:19:01,765
We're a hotel, after all.

331
00:19:06,227 --> 00:19:07,646
- Don't you agree?
- Hmm?

332
00:19:08,313 --> 00:19:09,522
Oh, sure.

333
00:19:09,814 --> 00:19:12,525
Yeah, we can't follow every trend.

334
00:19:13,151 --> 00:19:17,614
But shouldn't we change something
if the sales are dropping?

335
00:19:17,947 --> 00:19:21,618
Can't Marketing change its approach
to increase the sales?

336
00:19:22,786 --> 00:19:25,163
I've done some thinking

337
00:19:25,705 --> 00:19:28,583
and have you heard of the project,
"Ark of Taste"?

338
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,126
- "Ark"?
- "Ark of Taste"?

339
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:31,711
No, I've never heard of it.

340
00:19:31,795 --> 00:19:34,547
It's a project aimed to preserve
food varieties.

341
00:19:34,631 --> 00:19:37,050
Its list includes a few Korean items, too.

342
00:19:38,218 --> 00:19:40,220
You came so prepared.

343
00:19:41,554 --> 00:19:42,555
Let's see.

344
00:19:47,686 --> 00:19:50,313
It fits the values the hotel promotes

345
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:54,067
and it should also interest people
looking to spend their money meaningfully.

346
00:19:54,150 --> 00:19:57,570
This is going to be really hard.

347
00:19:58,321 --> 00:20:00,115
We'll have to travel all over the country!

348
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:02,158
I guess we'll really prove ourselves

349
00:20:02,242 --> 00:20:05,286
if we pull off such a complicated project.

350
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:06,579
Right?

351
00:20:25,932 --> 00:20:27,475
CONFERENCE ROOM

352
00:20:30,186 --> 00:20:33,022
The Senior Managing Director is
really looking forward to it.

353
00:20:33,106 --> 00:20:36,943
As you know, he likes to buy a bunch
for his friends and family.

354
00:20:37,652 --> 00:20:39,028
This is a good chance for us.

355
00:20:39,154 --> 00:20:41,573
Let's do well and impress Management.

356
00:20:41,656 --> 00:20:43,074
- Let's do that.
- Got it.

357
00:20:44,868 --> 00:20:45,994
Alright.

358
00:20:47,162 --> 00:20:49,080
How are you going to find producers?

359
00:20:49,330 --> 00:20:52,751
I'll make a list of products we can get
from our current suppliers first.

360
00:20:52,917 --> 00:20:54,669
I'll call the suppliers, then.

361
00:20:54,794 --> 00:20:57,756
And we'll need to travel
to find new suppliers for the others.

362
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:01,593
We can go to the market together.

363
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:03,011
Sure.

364
00:21:03,178 --> 00:21:04,304
Good luck, everyone.

365
00:21:04,387 --> 00:21:05,513
- Okay.
- Good work.

366
00:21:05,972 --> 00:21:07,974
HAVE A GOOD DAY. HAPPY MONDAY!

367
00:21:13,855 --> 00:21:14,856
Are you that happy?

368
00:21:15,482 --> 00:21:18,943
Not even Sua thinks so much
about what each emoji means.

369
00:21:19,027 --> 00:21:21,029
Why not? It's great. She sent me a heart.

370
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:25,200
Stars can be interpreted in so many ways

371
00:21:25,283 --> 00:21:27,702
but not a heart. That's just love.

372
00:21:30,497 --> 00:21:31,581
Enjoy it while you can.

373
00:21:31,664 --> 00:21:35,251
I'm so happy as your friend
that you're dating her now

374
00:21:35,335 --> 00:21:39,130
but as your co-CEO,
I'll have to ask you to select the pieces

375
00:21:39,214 --> 00:21:41,549
for the exhibition
before I throw your phone away.

376
00:21:41,633 --> 00:21:43,009
I was getting on that, okay?

377
00:21:48,389 --> 00:21:49,516
EXHIBITION PROPOSAL
FOR FINDING DAILY HARMONY

378
00:21:49,682 --> 00:21:50,767
PURPOSE OF THE EXHIBITION

379
00:21:50,850 --> 00:21:52,268
THE EXHIBITION STRIVES TO CONNECT
DESIGNERS' PHILOSOPHIES TO LIVING OBJECTS

380
00:21:52,352 --> 00:21:53,770
OUR LIVES ARE FILLED WITH HARMONIES
OF DIFFERENT RHYTHMS AND SENSES

381
00:21:53,853 --> 00:21:55,522
What's so hard about this?

382
00:21:55,605 --> 00:21:56,898
Everything's up to you.

383
00:21:56,981 --> 00:21:59,317
That's why it's harder.
Because there's no set client.

384
00:22:01,444 --> 00:22:02,445
Watch your step.

385
00:22:03,947 --> 00:22:05,156
- We're turning a corner.
- Yes.

386
00:22:06,199 --> 00:22:07,200
Go straight.

387
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:08,952
This way.

388
00:22:09,035 --> 00:22:10,495
- What are they doing?
- No idea.

389
00:22:11,246 --> 00:22:12,580
Okay.

390
00:22:12,664 --> 00:22:15,041
Put your hand down, and open your eyes.

391
00:22:16,709 --> 00:22:18,044
- Ta-da!
- Ta-da!

392
00:22:18,795 --> 00:22:22,382
Wait! Is this my chair?

393
00:22:22,924 --> 00:22:23,925
Really?

394
00:22:24,008 --> 00:22:25,510
Yeah, you can even write your name.

395
00:22:25,802 --> 00:22:27,053
We'll send it to your home.

396
00:22:27,136 --> 00:22:29,722
A comfortable seat
you can stay in for hours

397
00:22:29,806 --> 00:22:31,891
and a backrest that supports
your back perfectly!

398
00:22:31,975 --> 00:22:34,644
Give it a try. Chairs feel different
when you sit on them.

399
00:22:37,814 --> 00:22:40,650
It's so cushy!

400
00:22:40,733 --> 00:22:42,151
I love it so much!

401
00:22:43,903 --> 00:22:46,865
This is the best present I've ever gotten.

402
00:22:47,574 --> 00:22:48,616
- Really?
- Really?

403
00:22:49,033 --> 00:22:51,411
The gift givers seem even happier
than the recipient.

404
00:22:51,494 --> 00:22:52,954
That's how gifts work.

405
00:22:53,371 --> 00:22:55,957
No, you wouldn't know that.

406
00:22:56,040 --> 00:22:58,084
You only ever make things for your clients

407
00:22:58,167 --> 00:23:00,962
and give your parents
the ones with flaws or mistakes.

408
00:23:01,254 --> 00:23:05,091
You've never made anything
for anyone as a gift, have you?

409
00:23:08,219 --> 00:23:09,596
Yeah, I've never done that.

410
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:12,640
I've never felt that feeling.

411
00:23:13,892 --> 00:23:16,311
This is a perfect chance
to get me a gift, then.

412
00:23:16,895 --> 00:23:17,896
No.

413
00:23:18,396 --> 00:23:19,397
No, right?

414
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:21,482
No. Hey, you like the chair?

415
00:23:21,566 --> 00:23:22,901
THESE DESIGNS WILL BE MORE THAN OBJECTS.
THEY WILL SPARK EMPATHY AND INTERACTIONS

416
00:23:26,237 --> 00:23:28,031
I'm glad you got your idea.

417
00:23:28,239 --> 00:23:30,074
So, what are you building?

418
00:23:30,158 --> 00:23:31,200
I'll tell you later.

419
00:23:31,534 --> 00:23:33,786
I think I'll have a chance
to show it to you.

420
00:23:34,621 --> 00:23:37,248
- Are you heading home after dinner?
- Yeah.

421
00:23:37,415 --> 00:23:40,501
Hyun-min's been feeling down all day,
and I'm worried.

422
00:23:40,585 --> 00:23:42,045
I want to get her some good food.

423
00:23:42,253 --> 00:23:44,505
Don't forget your dinner.

424
00:23:44,589 --> 00:23:46,299
Okay, enjoy your dinner.

425
00:23:47,258 --> 00:23:48,259
Okay.

426
00:23:48,343 --> 00:23:50,011
A SEAT FOR LOVERS
THAT FEELS WARM AND AFFECTIONATE

427
00:23:50,094 --> 00:23:52,096
SOMETHING THAT WILL MOLD TO THE BODY
OVER TIME...

428
00:23:52,180 --> 00:23:54,223
HONEST AND COMFORTABLE

429
00:23:59,771 --> 00:24:01,147
Hey, sorry.

430
00:24:02,148 --> 00:24:03,983
Order whatever you want. It's on me.

431
00:24:04,233 --> 00:24:05,234
- Really?
- Yeah!

432
00:24:05,318 --> 00:24:06,778
- I'm getting drinks, then.
- Sure.

433
00:24:06,861 --> 00:24:10,490
Excuse me! A bottle of Baijiu, please!

434
00:24:10,573 --> 00:24:11,616
Okay.

435
00:24:11,699 --> 00:24:14,160
Why were you in the bathroom for so long?

436
00:24:14,369 --> 00:24:15,453
Is something wrong?

437
00:24:15,745 --> 00:24:18,790
No, I was just on the phone

438
00:24:19,540 --> 00:24:20,541
with Tae-seop.

439
00:24:21,626 --> 00:24:24,712
What's there to talk about
when the project's over?

440
00:24:24,837 --> 00:24:25,880
Well...

441
00:24:26,506 --> 00:24:27,507
Oh!

442
00:24:28,424 --> 00:24:29,425
Oh!

443
00:24:31,135 --> 00:24:34,138
I'm dating him now.

444
00:24:34,389 --> 00:24:35,848
Since the farewell party.

445
00:24:35,932 --> 00:24:38,476
No way! Did you two meet that night?

446
00:24:38,559 --> 00:24:42,355
Yeah, I was so late
that I wasn't sure if he'd still be there

447
00:24:42,438 --> 00:24:45,483
but there he was, dozing off
while waiting for me.

448
00:24:45,942 --> 00:24:46,943
Isn't that so funny?

449
00:24:47,652 --> 00:24:48,695
Sure.

450
00:24:50,238 --> 00:24:52,907
As long as he makes you laugh,
that's great.

451
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:56,160
Congratulations, Ui-yeong!

452
00:24:56,244 --> 00:24:57,370
Thanks.

453
00:24:57,996 --> 00:25:00,415
I can't believe
all those blind dates are finally over.

454
00:25:00,498 --> 00:25:01,749
I know!

455
00:25:02,667 --> 00:25:04,043
Congratulations!

456
00:25:04,335 --> 00:25:05,545
Our drink is here.

457
00:25:06,254 --> 00:25:07,547
Thank you.

458
00:25:07,630 --> 00:25:09,257
This calls for a celebration shot.

459
00:25:09,340 --> 00:25:10,341
Sure.

460
00:25:11,509 --> 00:25:13,052
Thank you.

461
00:25:17,473 --> 00:25:18,474
Gosh, I'm stuffed.

462
00:25:30,737 --> 00:25:33,406
So, how do you

463
00:25:33,906 --> 00:25:35,783
- do it?
- What?

464
00:25:36,576 --> 00:25:40,788
Build a close relationship based on trust?

465
00:25:41,539 --> 00:25:42,582
Trust?

466
00:25:43,249 --> 00:25:46,502
Trust just comes naturally
when you spend time together.

467
00:25:47,587 --> 00:25:52,925
They say it's different dating someone
and marrying someone.

468
00:25:53,926 --> 00:25:59,057
It seems like guys date certain women,
then marry other women.

469
00:25:59,140 --> 00:26:01,392
That's just what they all say.

470
00:26:01,559 --> 00:26:04,312
How can you predetermine
where your relationship is going

471
00:26:04,395 --> 00:26:05,688
before dating someone?

472
00:26:07,857 --> 00:26:09,108
But guys do that.

473
00:26:09,275 --> 00:26:12,153
What? Did someone say something to you?
Who was it?

474
00:26:15,907 --> 00:26:19,368
I recently met a guy on an app.

475
00:26:19,452 --> 00:26:21,079
- That dating app?
- No!

476
00:26:21,537 --> 00:26:24,248
It wasn't a dating app!

477
00:26:26,167 --> 00:26:27,794
Soonmu Market.

478
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:29,003
Soonmu?

479
00:26:29,837 --> 00:26:31,005
Oh.

480
00:26:33,174 --> 00:26:37,220
I guess a lot of people
meet people on it nowadays.

481
00:26:39,514 --> 00:26:43,601
Excuse me!
We'll get one more bottle Baijiu!

482
00:26:43,726 --> 00:26:45,686
- Okay.
- Hurry.

483
00:26:49,524 --> 00:26:50,525
Are you okay?

484
00:26:55,113 --> 00:26:56,906
- Are you done?
- Yeah.

485
00:26:58,616 --> 00:26:59,826
Is it really bad?

486
00:27:01,077 --> 00:27:02,745
I shouldn't have let you drink so much.

487
00:27:02,995 --> 00:27:04,163
Get in bed first.

488
00:27:07,333 --> 00:27:08,793
Seriously.

489
00:27:11,462 --> 00:27:14,924
Hyun-min, I've known you long enough.

490
00:27:15,091 --> 00:27:17,718
I know you're different

491
00:27:18,177 --> 00:27:20,721
but you're not the type to betray anyone.

492
00:27:21,055 --> 00:27:23,975
If a man can't see that, just let him go.
You got that?

493
00:27:24,267 --> 00:27:25,810
He's already gone.

494
00:27:26,894 --> 00:27:30,022
- I'm taking a day off tomorrow.
- Okay.

495
00:27:30,523 --> 00:27:32,108
Feel better.

496
00:27:32,191 --> 00:27:35,361
I'll leave some water and a hangover cure.
Take it, okay?

497
00:27:42,285 --> 00:27:43,327
Alright...

498
00:27:54,088 --> 00:27:56,174
Gosh, she's been drinking so much.

499
00:28:27,288 --> 00:28:29,957
You're so stupid! You're such a chicken!

500
00:28:30,041 --> 00:28:34,879
It seems like guys date certain women,
then marry other women.

501
00:28:35,046 --> 00:28:37,131
I got the series second-hand
over the weekend.

502
00:28:37,340 --> 00:28:39,467
You know the girl I sold my comics to?

503
00:28:40,134 --> 00:28:41,886
Hey, forget it.
You can't date someone like that.

504
00:28:41,969 --> 00:28:43,638
She'd always make you anxious
if you dated her.

505
00:28:43,721 --> 00:28:45,473
I recently met a guy on an app.

506
00:28:45,556 --> 00:28:47,308
Soonmu Market.

507
00:28:48,059 --> 00:28:49,685
You know the girl I sold my comics to?

508
00:28:52,813 --> 00:28:57,777
DEUKGEUN DEUKGEUN GYM

509
00:28:58,277 --> 00:29:00,279
I'm home.

510
00:29:00,613 --> 00:29:01,697
Hey.

511
00:29:03,032 --> 00:29:04,075
Mom.

512
00:29:06,619 --> 00:29:08,287
Why is the world so small?

513
00:29:08,371 --> 00:29:11,707
- Why?
- I think my friend and my coworker...

514
00:29:12,458 --> 00:29:13,584
have a thing going on.

515
00:29:13,668 --> 00:29:15,086
Who? Seung-jun?

516
00:29:15,753 --> 00:29:17,546
Did you set them up?

517
00:29:17,672 --> 00:29:18,714
No.

518
00:29:19,757 --> 00:29:23,344
I think I actually might've gotten
in their way.

519
00:29:23,427 --> 00:29:24,679
What?

520
00:29:25,972 --> 00:29:29,225
I know you're close to them,
but you're not in this relationship.

521
00:29:29,433 --> 00:29:30,893
Don't get involved, okay?

522
00:29:32,061 --> 00:29:35,356
Maybe they didn't tell you
because they weren't serious.

523
00:29:38,317 --> 00:29:40,695
Yeah, this is between them.

524
00:29:41,028 --> 00:29:43,239
It's not like I can fix anything
by getting involved.

525
00:29:50,204 --> 00:29:52,957
We got the other items sorted

526
00:29:53,040 --> 00:29:54,834
so we just need to find tiger cattle beef.

527
00:29:54,959 --> 00:29:56,043
Alright, let's go.

528
00:29:56,127 --> 00:29:59,046
One person at this big market has to know
a local tiger cattle farmer.

529
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:00,965
- First...
- Let's see.

530
00:30:01,048 --> 00:30:02,174
Should we start from here?

531
00:30:02,258 --> 00:30:03,467
Okay.

532
00:30:05,052 --> 00:30:07,138
- Hello.
- Hello.

533
00:30:07,305 --> 00:30:09,515
- Do you sell tiger cattle beef?
- No.

534
00:30:09,598 --> 00:30:12,268
- Do you know anyone who does?
- Not at this market.

535
00:30:13,019 --> 00:30:14,395
MEAT FROM FEMALE KOREAN COWS

536
00:30:14,478 --> 00:30:16,314
- Hello!
- Hello.

537
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:18,941
Do you sell tiger cattle beef here?

538
00:30:19,025 --> 00:30:20,234
No, we don't.

539
00:30:20,318 --> 00:30:21,652
- Really?
- No.

540
00:30:21,861 --> 00:30:23,612
- Thank you, have a good day.
- Bye.

541
00:30:23,863 --> 00:30:25,614
LIST OF BUTCHERS

542
00:30:27,116 --> 00:30:28,576
- Hello, sir.
- Hi.

543
00:30:28,659 --> 00:30:30,453
Do you know a tiger cattle farmer?

544
00:30:30,536 --> 00:30:32,580
- No, I don't.
- No?

545
00:30:32,872 --> 00:30:34,540
Thank you.

546
00:30:34,707 --> 00:30:35,875
That's a no.

547
00:30:36,250 --> 00:30:37,293
We don't sell it.

548
00:30:37,376 --> 00:30:39,587
Okay, thank you. Have a good day.

549
00:30:43,341 --> 00:30:45,384
- Did you find any?
- No.

550
00:30:45,468 --> 00:30:46,927
Let's check the rest.

551
00:30:47,011 --> 00:30:49,138
- I'll go this way, then.
- I'll text you.

552
00:30:53,601 --> 00:30:54,727
We don't sell it.

553
00:30:55,644 --> 00:30:56,812
Okay, thank you.

554
00:30:57,271 --> 00:30:59,774
LIST OF BUTCHERS

555
00:31:00,691 --> 00:31:02,485
We've checked almost every shop.

556
00:31:02,568 --> 00:31:04,195
I know. Why is it so hard to find?

557
00:31:04,945 --> 00:31:07,698
It says there's a butcher shop here.

558
00:31:07,782 --> 00:31:09,784
Really? I thought I just saw an herb shop.

559
00:31:10,284 --> 00:31:13,913
Let me go to Mr. Shin's shop
before it closes, then.

560
00:31:14,038 --> 00:31:16,248
- Call me if you find anything.
- Okay.

561
00:31:24,548 --> 00:31:27,718
OREUM BUTCHER SHOP

562
00:31:39,105 --> 00:31:40,648
Hello, sir.

563
00:31:40,731 --> 00:31:42,858
I'm from The Hills Hotel.

564
00:31:43,943 --> 00:31:46,404
- You want anything?
- No, not now.

565
00:31:46,487 --> 00:31:51,033
I just wanted to ask
if you know of a tiger cattle farm.

566
00:31:52,243 --> 00:31:54,787
Tiger cattle? Let's see.

567
00:31:55,496 --> 00:31:59,041
I can't remember if Mr. Choi raises
tiger cattle or black cows.

568
00:31:59,125 --> 00:32:02,169
Do you know someone? Where is his farm?

569
00:32:02,253 --> 00:32:05,464
It's somewhere in Gangwon-do
or Gyeongsango-do.

570
00:32:08,300 --> 00:32:09,552
I suddenly can't remember it.

571
00:32:10,302 --> 00:32:12,888
Maybe it's because I haven't made
a lot of sales today.

572
00:32:12,972 --> 00:32:14,807
Oh, gosh, silly me.

573
00:32:17,268 --> 00:32:20,980
I want to get some Korean beef to grill.

574
00:32:21,063 --> 00:32:22,773
I'll take three pounds

575
00:32:23,399 --> 00:32:26,318
of the best part.
Maybe that'll help you remember.

576
00:32:29,405 --> 00:32:30,906
I'm not sure if I'll remember.

577
00:32:37,955 --> 00:32:41,459
Here's three pounds of sirloin
and his number.

578
00:32:42,460 --> 00:32:45,254
Thank you so much! You saved my life.

579
00:32:45,337 --> 00:32:46,922
No, it's nothing.

580
00:32:47,465 --> 00:32:51,594
By the way, Mr. Choi can be a real Grinch.

581
00:32:51,677 --> 00:32:54,096
I'm not sure
if he'll get along with you two.

582
00:32:59,852 --> 00:33:02,104
What's wrong?
Are you worried about what he said?

583
00:33:03,564 --> 00:33:07,318
Yeah, we have a lot to discuss.
His personality matters.

584
00:33:08,027 --> 00:33:11,947
That's true, but you can't raise
a rare breed if you're easygoing.

585
00:33:13,157 --> 00:33:16,785
He has the upper hand in this deal,
so we'll just have to go along with him.

586
00:33:16,869 --> 00:33:18,537
I know, but...

587
00:33:19,413 --> 00:33:21,290
Don't worry about it.

588
00:33:21,540 --> 00:33:23,167
I'll arrange the meeting

589
00:33:23,250 --> 00:33:25,836
and be in charge of all communications.

590
00:33:26,795 --> 00:33:27,838
Okay.

591
00:33:29,673 --> 00:33:32,510
By the way,
you look really happy these days.

592
00:33:33,385 --> 00:33:34,678
- Do I?
- Yeah.

593
00:33:36,514 --> 00:33:39,391
I don't know
why I feel so motivated at my job lately.

594
00:33:41,602 --> 00:33:44,104
But we have to head back and wrap it up.

595
00:33:44,688 --> 00:33:46,565
Let's get some coffee and head back.

596
00:33:46,941 --> 00:33:48,526
- Oh, I...
- Come on!

597
00:33:48,609 --> 00:33:51,153
It's on me.

598
00:33:55,407 --> 00:33:57,618
- "This is..."
- We need some coffee.

599
00:33:57,701 --> 00:33:58,869
Choose what you want.

600
00:34:01,664 --> 00:34:05,084
- Hey.
- Here you go.

601
00:34:05,167 --> 00:34:06,377
- Okay.
- Wait.

602
00:34:09,171 --> 00:34:11,549
I have to take this call.

603
00:34:11,632 --> 00:34:14,218
I'll get an iced Americano.

604
00:34:16,262 --> 00:34:17,513
- Hello.
- Hey

605
00:34:17,763 --> 00:34:19,557
I'll get two iced Americanos to go.

606
00:34:20,057 --> 00:34:21,058
Okay.

607
00:34:23,435 --> 00:34:24,478
Here.

608
00:34:25,020 --> 00:34:26,063
Thanks.

609
00:34:29,149 --> 00:34:30,401
How have you been?

610
00:34:30,484 --> 00:34:32,444
Did you go home safely that day?

611
00:34:33,529 --> 00:34:35,364
Yeah, that was days ago.

612
00:34:36,574 --> 00:34:38,492
How do you think I've been?

613
00:34:40,953 --> 00:34:42,621
Oh, sorry.

614
00:34:43,706 --> 00:34:46,834
No need to be sorry.
You just followed your heart.

615
00:34:48,919 --> 00:34:51,463
I've been busy lately.
I had no time to be sad.

616
00:34:51,547 --> 00:34:55,050
So, did you land a role
after that audition?

617
00:34:55,134 --> 00:34:57,261
Yeah, I think so.

618
00:34:57,344 --> 00:34:58,762
That's so great.

619
00:35:00,514 --> 00:35:03,309
And you? Are you dating Tae-seop now?

620
00:35:05,894 --> 00:35:08,147
Yeah, we're dating now.

621
00:35:10,983 --> 00:35:13,152
- That's why you haven't been here?
- Hmm?

622
00:35:13,319 --> 00:35:14,987
Did he tell you not to come here

623
00:35:15,654 --> 00:35:17,489
or are you giving me space to get closure?

624
00:35:19,992 --> 00:35:21,577
Nothing has to change.

625
00:35:21,785 --> 00:35:24,288
We're just back to being friends.

626
00:35:27,166 --> 00:35:28,959
It's not like we broke up after dating.

627
00:35:29,043 --> 00:35:31,545
Don't be so old-fashioned.
Times have changed.

628
00:35:34,089 --> 00:35:37,217
I promise not to cross the line.

629
00:35:37,718 --> 00:35:38,802
I won't bother you.

630
00:35:39,637 --> 00:35:40,679
All good now?

631
00:35:44,350 --> 00:35:46,727
Okay, then.

632
00:35:46,935 --> 00:35:47,936
Yeah.

633
00:35:49,271 --> 00:35:50,939
Is the coffee ready?

634
00:35:51,023 --> 00:35:52,024
Yeah.

635
00:35:53,192 --> 00:35:54,902
- See you around.
- Bye.

636
00:36:02,576 --> 00:36:06,497
So, we've decided to give you the role,
Ji-su.

637
00:36:07,831 --> 00:36:08,957
Mr. Shin?

638
00:36:09,875 --> 00:36:12,211
Oh, thank you for the opportunity.

639
00:36:17,007 --> 00:36:18,634
Oh, hello.

640
00:36:20,177 --> 00:36:21,512
I didn't know Ji-su was here.

641
00:36:22,137 --> 00:36:23,347
Is this a surprise?

642
00:36:23,514 --> 00:36:25,099
I don't like surprises.

643
00:36:26,225 --> 00:36:28,268
Oh, I caught you off-guard. Sorry.

644
00:36:28,352 --> 00:36:29,728
Have a seat.

645
00:36:45,828 --> 00:36:48,664
I guess you don't talk about acting
with your mother at all.

646
00:36:49,832 --> 00:36:50,833
Why not?

647
00:36:51,542 --> 00:36:52,543
Right.

648
00:36:53,377 --> 00:36:54,545
What's so surprising?

649
00:36:54,628 --> 00:36:56,922
Do you talk about directing
with your mother?

650
00:36:59,174 --> 00:37:01,385
I see what you mean
now that you've put it that way.

651
00:37:02,136 --> 00:37:03,804
I've built my acting career by myself

652
00:37:04,179 --> 00:37:05,639
and I plan on continuing to do so.

653
00:37:06,223 --> 00:37:08,559
We're not related by blood

654
00:37:08,934 --> 00:37:10,769
but he's just like me, straightforward.

655
00:37:11,019 --> 00:37:14,732
Don't tell me you hired Ji-su

656
00:37:14,898 --> 00:37:16,608
because I'm reviewing your next project.

657
00:37:16,984 --> 00:37:18,318
Not at all.

658
00:37:19,611 --> 00:37:22,197
He fit the role best.

659
00:37:22,364 --> 00:37:23,991
I shouldn't have been invited, then.

660
00:37:24,074 --> 00:37:25,534
People will get the wrong idea.

661
00:37:25,617 --> 00:37:27,703
And it's Ji-su's first drama.

662
00:37:27,995 --> 00:37:30,456
I'm sure he'd rather talk to you
in private.

663
00:37:31,457 --> 00:37:33,417
He really doesn't understand actors.

664
00:37:33,792 --> 00:37:35,127
I guess so.

665
00:37:35,627 --> 00:37:38,380
Let me know anytime
you want to talk to me.

666
00:37:39,381 --> 00:37:41,258
Okay, thank you.

667
00:37:47,222 --> 00:37:48,974
I was going to pay for dinner.

668
00:37:49,224 --> 00:37:51,101
I hope you enjoy my script.

669
00:37:51,185 --> 00:37:52,686
I'll enjoy it if it's good.

670
00:37:53,896 --> 00:37:55,522
Your car's waiting. You should go.

671
00:37:55,689 --> 00:37:56,857
I need to talk to Ji-su.

672
00:37:56,940 --> 00:37:58,150
Okay, goodnight.

673
00:37:59,485 --> 00:38:00,694
See you on the set, Ji-su.

674
00:38:01,069 --> 00:38:03,113
Okay, goodnight.

675
00:38:07,951 --> 00:38:11,580
I'll do my best
to prevent these meetings from happening

676
00:38:11,997 --> 00:38:14,625
but we can't avoid them completely
if we're in the same field.

677
00:38:15,083 --> 00:38:16,084
I'm aware of that.

678
00:38:16,168 --> 00:38:19,338
Take advantage of it next time.

679
00:38:19,421 --> 00:38:20,672
I'm glad you could keep calm.

680
00:38:21,340 --> 00:38:24,301
You did the same. You stayed calm.

681
00:38:25,385 --> 00:38:26,386
It's nothing.

682
00:38:27,012 --> 00:38:28,514
Congratulations on your new role.

683
00:38:28,597 --> 00:38:30,390
I'll see how you do on TV.

684
00:38:30,682 --> 00:38:31,683
Bye.

685
00:38:49,785 --> 00:38:50,869
Did you get some rest?

686
00:38:51,829 --> 00:38:54,164
Yeah, I feel a lot better now.

687
00:38:55,040 --> 00:38:57,543
I can't let a man make me have regrets.

688
00:38:58,168 --> 00:39:00,838
I've even put the comics back on sale
on Soonmu Market.

689
00:39:01,547 --> 00:39:04,132
I guess you're really over him.

690
00:39:04,550 --> 00:39:08,136
It's not like I didn't try.

691
00:39:08,470 --> 00:39:11,807
I had to block him
in fear that I'd drunk-call him.

692
00:39:13,684 --> 00:39:17,813
So, you blocked him
because you were worried you'd call him?

693
00:39:18,939 --> 00:39:22,818
I also didn't want to get my hopes up
and have him not call me.

694
00:39:23,068 --> 00:39:24,236
It was for both reasons.

695
00:39:30,534 --> 00:39:32,578
No, mind your own business.

696
00:39:32,828 --> 00:39:36,123
You're not a part of this situation.
Leave it to the two.

697
00:39:42,629 --> 00:39:45,382
DEUKGEUN DEUKGEUN GYM

698
00:39:45,465 --> 00:39:46,633
Seung-jun!

699
00:39:46,717 --> 00:39:47,718
What?

700
00:39:47,885 --> 00:39:49,428
Tell me. Hyun...

701
00:39:49,803 --> 00:39:52,806
No, the Soonmu Market girl.
Do you still like her?

702
00:39:53,056 --> 00:39:54,683
Why are you suddenly asking me that?

703
00:39:54,766 --> 00:39:56,935
Just tell me! Do you like her or not?

704
00:39:57,811 --> 00:40:01,607
I do! How can I stop liking her
just overnight?

705
00:40:01,815 --> 00:40:03,525
You know I'm not that cool.

706
00:40:03,817 --> 00:40:04,860
I'm glad.

707
00:40:05,319 --> 00:40:06,570
Come with me.

708
00:40:07,487 --> 00:40:08,530
Is this her?

709
00:40:10,532 --> 00:40:12,784
Yeah, it is. Our memories!

710
00:40:14,244 --> 00:40:15,537
She's really ready to move on!

711
00:40:15,621 --> 00:40:17,247
Pull yourself together!

712
00:40:17,331 --> 00:40:18,999
Why do you think she's selling them?

713
00:40:19,082 --> 00:40:21,084
Because she's trying to get over you!

714
00:40:21,835 --> 00:40:23,086
Get some money ready.

715
00:40:23,545 --> 00:40:24,588
I'll buy them.

716
00:40:24,796 --> 00:40:27,257
I'll buy the comics and everything else
you're selling.

717
00:40:27,549 --> 00:40:28,675
Can we meet somewhere?

718
00:40:31,970 --> 00:40:33,805
How did you know it was her?

719
00:40:33,889 --> 00:40:36,350
Huh? Well, I...

720
00:40:36,767 --> 00:40:39,686
I'll tell you once things work out, okay?

721
00:40:53,116 --> 00:40:55,118
She must've gotten home hours ago.

722
00:40:57,704 --> 00:40:59,122
UI-YEONG

723
00:41:00,207 --> 00:41:01,208
Oh!

724
00:41:05,045 --> 00:41:08,215
Where are you?
Why didn't you read my messages?

725
00:41:08,715 --> 00:41:10,676
I met Seung-jun after work.

726
00:41:10,759 --> 00:41:12,177
Oh, Seung-jun?

727
00:41:12,678 --> 00:41:13,679
Then...

728
00:41:14,763 --> 00:41:16,682
- what about me?
- What?

729
00:41:17,140 --> 00:41:18,475
Didn't you miss me?

730
00:41:19,101 --> 00:41:21,228
I missed you.

731
00:41:25,148 --> 00:41:26,525
Say that again.

732
00:41:27,985 --> 00:41:29,111
What a nice thing to hear.

733
00:41:31,029 --> 00:41:32,614
I miss you, Ui-yeong.

734
00:41:33,365 --> 00:41:34,408
Come and see me.

735
00:41:42,124 --> 00:41:44,292
Did all your employees go home?

736
00:41:44,418 --> 00:41:45,419
Yeah.

737
00:41:46,628 --> 00:41:49,881
So, this is what your office looks like.

738
00:41:51,091 --> 00:41:52,175
It's stunning.

739
00:41:53,176 --> 00:41:55,262
This is where we work on documents

740
00:41:55,429 --> 00:41:57,222
design things, and have meetings.

741
00:41:58,056 --> 00:42:00,100
Over here. This is my desk.

742
00:42:00,225 --> 00:42:01,977
I see. That's the best spot.

743
00:42:04,438 --> 00:42:07,315
It seems like such a chill office.

744
00:42:07,983 --> 00:42:12,446
We have to air it out often
because we have a lot of sawdust.

745
00:42:12,529 --> 00:42:15,532
- I see.
- And this is the woodworking workshop.

746
00:42:15,615 --> 00:42:16,700
The workshop?

747
00:42:18,952 --> 00:42:21,121
You might get splinters,
as it's not processed.

748
00:42:21,204 --> 00:42:22,330
I see.

749
00:42:22,956 --> 00:42:24,624
It's too dangerous. Here.

750
00:42:27,502 --> 00:42:29,880
There are so many interesting tools.

751
00:42:32,132 --> 00:42:34,426
This is the table saw for cutting blocks.

752
00:42:34,676 --> 00:42:35,719
Table saw?

753
00:42:36,344 --> 00:42:37,763
And this is a band saw.

754
00:42:38,013 --> 00:42:39,097
A band saw.

755
00:42:39,181 --> 00:42:42,100
And this is a drilling machine
for drilling holes.

756
00:42:42,184 --> 00:42:43,685
A drilling machine.

757
00:42:44,728 --> 00:42:46,313
I can't remember that. It's too hard.

758
00:42:47,397 --> 00:42:50,609
Oh, can you help me with something
since you're already here?

759
00:42:50,776 --> 00:42:51,902
What is it?

760
00:43:07,167 --> 00:43:10,337
I need measurements for a sample chair
to submit for the exhibition.

761
00:43:11,838 --> 00:43:15,759
I feel like I'm giving too many details
about me.

762
00:43:16,384 --> 00:43:18,553
No, I still have a long way to go.

763
00:43:21,264 --> 00:43:22,474
I want to know you more.

764
00:43:31,274 --> 00:43:34,444
I don't think we should just meet
on weekends. I'm too busy.

765
00:43:34,778 --> 00:43:36,655
Let's just meet whenever we want.

766
00:43:36,738 --> 00:43:38,073
That sounds like a plan.

767
00:43:50,836 --> 00:43:53,463
Mr. Song!

768
00:43:54,339 --> 00:43:56,341
Mr. Song? Did he go home?

769
00:43:57,384 --> 00:43:59,052
Man, we got you snacks.

770
00:44:02,556 --> 00:44:04,141
That leaves us with no choice.

771
00:44:04,432 --> 00:44:07,686
We'll need some beer if he's not here.

772
00:44:07,769 --> 00:44:09,271
Jin-su, get some from the store!

773
00:44:09,354 --> 00:44:11,606
Okay, you like beer, right?

774
00:44:11,940 --> 00:44:13,024
Are we allowed to drink?

775
00:44:13,108 --> 00:44:14,693
Of course not.

776
00:44:15,610 --> 00:44:18,280
Mr. Song lets us do anything here

777
00:44:18,405 --> 00:44:21,575
but drink or date.
Those are non-negotiables.

778
00:44:21,658 --> 00:44:26,538
Why? Because it's too thrilling
that you get hot.

779
00:44:27,164 --> 00:44:28,248
It's dangerous.

780
00:44:31,418 --> 00:44:33,336
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

781
00:44:39,676 --> 00:44:40,844
It's extra good today.

782
00:44:40,927 --> 00:44:42,429
This is the best!

783
00:44:42,512 --> 00:44:43,847
- Let's dig in.
- Dig in!

784
00:44:44,097 --> 00:44:45,348
My legs hurt.

785
00:44:45,432 --> 00:44:46,933
- Your legs?
- Yeah, hold on.

786
00:44:50,312 --> 00:44:52,314
What was that?

787
00:44:53,732 --> 00:44:54,858
Who's there?

788
00:44:55,025 --> 00:44:57,235
- That's scary.
- Who's there?

789
00:44:59,112 --> 00:45:00,113
Bo-yoon...

790
00:45:00,488 --> 00:45:02,574
Where are you going? Sae-byeok?

791
00:45:03,950 --> 00:45:04,993
Darn it.

792
00:45:10,707 --> 00:45:11,708
Huh?

793
00:45:12,834 --> 00:45:14,127
- Jin-su.
- Yeah?

794
00:45:14,878 --> 00:45:15,921
Go.

795
00:45:16,046 --> 00:45:17,214
Darn it!

796
00:45:17,756 --> 00:45:18,840
Come out!

797
00:45:19,257 --> 00:45:20,425
I'm calling the cops!

798
00:45:21,176 --> 00:45:22,302
We have weapons!

799
00:45:27,182 --> 00:45:28,683
You'd better come out in three.

800
00:45:29,434 --> 00:45:30,477
One.

801
00:45:30,894 --> 00:45:31,895
Two.

802
00:45:32,270 --> 00:45:34,105
Three!

803
00:45:34,522 --> 00:45:36,650
Hey, guys.

804
00:45:36,775 --> 00:45:38,610
What are you doing there?

805
00:45:38,693 --> 00:45:40,403
- Huh?
- Gosh, my legs.

806
00:45:40,487 --> 00:45:41,696
Oh, hi.

807
00:45:41,863 --> 00:45:43,406
Huh? Ui-yeong!

808
00:45:44,282 --> 00:45:45,492
Hi, Sae-byeok.

809
00:45:46,034 --> 00:45:49,204
It's great seeing you fitting in so well

810
00:45:49,579 --> 00:45:50,664
at your new job.

811
00:45:51,414 --> 00:45:54,042
What are you two doing here?

812
00:45:56,127 --> 00:45:57,128
We...

813
00:45:58,004 --> 00:45:59,422
We're dating.

814
00:46:00,674 --> 00:46:02,801
Ui-yeong and Mr. Song?

815
00:46:03,760 --> 00:46:06,179
You said no dating in office!

816
00:46:06,554 --> 00:46:08,556
That's too dangerous!

817
00:46:09,307 --> 00:46:12,560
You guys are drinking here, too!
That's also dangerous.

818
00:46:14,396 --> 00:46:15,397
Huh?

819
00:46:20,235 --> 00:46:21,278
Congratulations.

820
00:46:45,093 --> 00:46:46,261
Ms. Big Discounts?

821
00:46:46,970 --> 00:46:48,179
Mr. Choco Killer?

822
00:46:50,015 --> 00:46:51,141
Choco...

823
00:47:01,651 --> 00:47:02,652
I knew it.

824
00:47:02,861 --> 00:47:05,488
You don't even eat chocolate!
How are you "Choco Killer"?

825
00:47:06,990 --> 00:47:10,368
Using someone else's account

826
00:47:10,452 --> 00:47:13,538
can get you banned from the app for life.
You know that?

827
00:47:13,621 --> 00:47:15,332
No, I don't. Report me if you want.

828
00:47:15,415 --> 00:47:18,376
Soonmu Market just reminds me of you,
anyway.

829
00:47:18,585 --> 00:47:21,338
I'll delete my account and delete the app.

830
00:47:22,339 --> 00:47:23,673
After this deal.

831
00:47:27,844 --> 00:47:30,096
It's 50,000 won. The deal's done.
Give me the money.

832
00:47:33,016 --> 00:47:34,184
Not just like this.

833
00:47:34,267 --> 00:47:35,477
Make another bet with me.

834
00:47:35,560 --> 00:47:37,187
If you beat me, you get 100,000 won.

835
00:47:37,354 --> 00:47:38,813
No, I'll give you 150,000 won.

836
00:47:39,064 --> 00:47:42,025
You think we're at a market? Forget it.

837
00:47:42,108 --> 00:47:44,319
How much more do I need to pay
for you to take it?

838
00:47:46,821 --> 00:47:48,531
What if you win?

839
00:47:48,948 --> 00:47:51,034
I know you're trying to get something
out of this.

840
00:47:54,871 --> 00:47:55,872
Just...

841
00:47:57,415 --> 00:47:58,666
hear me out.

842
00:48:00,251 --> 00:48:01,336
That's all I need.

843
00:48:06,508 --> 00:48:08,093
I was too embarrassed to say this

844
00:48:08,551 --> 00:48:10,053
but I was on the basketball team.

845
00:48:10,428 --> 00:48:12,055
I was training to go pro until college

846
00:48:12,138 --> 00:48:13,932
but had to quit after a crucifix injury.

847
00:48:15,183 --> 00:48:17,936
That was when I started being so careful,
mentally and physically.

848
00:48:18,186 --> 00:48:20,730
That was why I easily assumed things
about you.

849
00:48:20,939 --> 00:48:23,525
I was afraid I'd get hurt,
so I hurt you first.

850
00:48:25,402 --> 00:48:26,403
I'm sorry.

851
00:48:27,404 --> 00:48:30,365
I'm only supposed to hear you out
if you win.

852
00:48:30,448 --> 00:48:31,533
Tell me after you win.

853
00:48:31,616 --> 00:48:33,368
I can't hear you!

854
00:48:33,451 --> 00:48:34,452
Come on. Go.

855
00:49:15,618 --> 00:49:16,619
TIME'S UP

856
00:49:40,977 --> 00:49:44,481
The moment you give up, the game's over.

857
00:49:52,822 --> 00:49:54,115
I really like you.

858
00:49:55,825 --> 00:49:57,535
I really wanted to tell you this.

859
00:50:12,175 --> 00:50:13,843
Was the trip here okay?

860
00:50:14,469 --> 00:50:16,513
- It was okay.
- Here.

861
00:50:18,431 --> 00:50:19,432
Hello.

862
00:50:19,516 --> 00:50:20,517
- He's here.
- Hello.

863
00:50:20,600 --> 00:50:21,684
Nice to meet you.

864
00:50:21,768 --> 00:50:22,852
IDAE FARM'S SPECIAL STRATEGY
WITH THE SPECIAL TIGER CATTLES

865
00:50:22,936 --> 00:50:23,978
This is amazing.

866
00:50:24,521 --> 00:50:25,605
I know!

867
00:50:25,688 --> 00:50:27,398
My tiger cattles are bred

868
00:50:27,482 --> 00:50:32,195
with the healthiest cows
from all over the country

869
00:50:32,278 --> 00:50:33,613
directly at the farm.

870
00:50:33,696 --> 00:50:36,407
I raise each one with love,
like it's my own child.

871
00:50:36,491 --> 00:50:40,161
We'll make sure to treat
your precious tiger cattles well.

872
00:50:40,662 --> 00:50:42,413
As you should!

873
00:50:44,541 --> 00:50:46,668
You know, miss

874
00:50:46,751 --> 00:50:49,921
your beautiful, sparkly eyes

875
00:50:50,171 --> 00:50:53,841
look just like my tiger cattles' eyes!

876
00:50:53,925 --> 00:50:55,009
Your tiger cattles?

877
00:50:56,553 --> 00:50:57,887
I see the resemblance.

878
00:50:57,971 --> 00:51:00,682
That's a first for me. Thank you.

879
00:51:01,891 --> 00:51:06,312
I'm really thirsty.
Is there anything to drink?

880
00:51:06,396 --> 00:51:07,647
Something sweet.

881
00:51:07,730 --> 00:51:10,733
I'll get some juice, then.

882
00:51:10,817 --> 00:51:12,777
We'll get some cookies, too.

883
00:51:12,860 --> 00:51:15,196
- We'll be right back.
- I feel bad now.

884
00:51:15,280 --> 00:51:17,740
We should've prepared some in advance.
We're sorry.

885
00:51:20,326 --> 00:51:22,036
He's not grumpy at all.

886
00:51:22,370 --> 00:51:23,705
I know!

887
00:51:23,788 --> 00:51:24,831
I'm so glad.

888
00:51:25,999 --> 00:51:27,458
- Hey
- Yes?

889
00:51:27,542 --> 00:51:31,754
I'm looking for a long-term partner
whom I can trust.

890
00:51:31,838 --> 00:51:33,256
We're looking for the same.

891
00:51:33,339 --> 00:51:35,049
We can start with this project

892
00:51:35,258 --> 00:51:38,261
and build a long-term partnership.

893
00:51:38,344 --> 00:51:39,637
- By the way
- Yes?

894
00:51:40,054 --> 00:51:43,975
you know the lady with the bright eyes?

895
00:51:44,058 --> 00:51:45,059
Bright eyes?

896
00:51:45,852 --> 00:51:47,020
Oh, yes.

897
00:51:47,103 --> 00:51:50,982
Does she have a boyfriend?

898
00:51:51,566 --> 00:51:53,568
Why are you asking that?

899
00:51:53,985 --> 00:51:57,030
My youngest son is single

900
00:51:57,113 --> 00:51:59,991
because he only ever cares
about our tiger cattles.

901
00:52:00,074 --> 00:52:01,701
He hasn't dated anyone in forever.

902
00:52:01,784 --> 00:52:06,122
It'd be nice to get
the youngsters to talk business

903
00:52:06,205 --> 00:52:10,835
and maybe bond over talks about life.

904
00:52:10,918 --> 00:52:13,379
There's no partnership

905
00:52:13,463 --> 00:52:16,758
stronger and more solid than that!

906
00:52:16,841 --> 00:52:18,009
Oh, I see.

907
00:52:18,885 --> 00:52:21,471
That's what you mean by a partnership.

908
00:52:26,309 --> 00:52:27,310
Okay.

909
00:52:29,604 --> 00:52:30,980
Damn it.

910
00:52:37,654 --> 00:52:39,530
Things went so smoothly.

911
00:52:40,657 --> 00:52:43,910
I'll take care of discussing the details
and signing the contract...

912
00:52:43,993 --> 00:52:45,662
No, that's okay.

913
00:52:47,038 --> 00:52:48,539
Let's have Ui-yeong do it.

914
00:52:51,501 --> 00:52:52,627
- Sorry?
- Hmm?

915
00:52:52,710 --> 00:52:56,214
But Na-ri found the farm

916
00:52:56,422 --> 00:52:59,217
arranged the meeting,
and did the research.

917
00:52:59,300 --> 00:53:00,885
I know

918
00:53:01,969 --> 00:53:03,262
but just do it, okay?

919
00:53:03,346 --> 00:53:05,848
We need to work on the recipes, too

920
00:53:05,932 --> 00:53:07,975
and I know Chef Park trusts you.

921
00:53:08,059 --> 00:53:10,395
- But...
- And Na-ri

922
00:53:10,853 --> 00:53:12,522
- good work.
- Mr. Oh!

923
00:53:13,272 --> 00:53:16,317
Why am I always tired these days?
Maybe I have a bad liver.

924
00:53:27,328 --> 00:53:30,206
So, I'll have to meet them
tomorrow after work.

925
00:53:31,833 --> 00:53:35,128
But Na-ri won't hand over anything.

926
00:53:35,211 --> 00:53:37,422
She must be really disappointed.

927
00:53:37,505 --> 00:53:40,758
It won't be easy to start from scratch
and be ready in a day.

928
00:53:40,842 --> 00:53:44,053
But I feel better after telling you this.

929
00:53:44,887 --> 00:53:47,014
Even though nothing's sorted.

930
00:53:48,808 --> 00:53:51,060
You can tell me anything anytime.

931
00:53:51,227 --> 00:53:53,604
Oh, why don't I pick you up
after work tomorrow?

932
00:53:54,147 --> 00:53:56,607
No, I don't even know when I'll be done.

933
00:53:56,691 --> 00:53:58,067
Let's just meet on the weekend.

934
00:53:58,609 --> 00:54:00,319
Are you working until late today?

935
00:54:00,403 --> 00:54:03,614
Yeah, but it's not so bad
now that I've delegated the work.

936
00:54:03,698 --> 00:54:06,868
I'll call you again when I get home.

937
00:54:07,076 --> 00:54:08,119
Okay.

938
00:54:15,293 --> 00:54:17,754
HANKUK UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

939
00:54:17,837 --> 00:54:21,674
HANKUK UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL
DIRECTOR INAUGURATION CEREMONY

940
00:54:21,758 --> 00:54:22,800
Hello.

941
00:54:23,426 --> 00:54:24,427
Congratulations.

942
00:54:25,136 --> 00:54:26,137
Thank you.

943
00:54:26,929 --> 00:54:29,390
- It's an honor to meet you.
- I'm flattered. Thank you.

944
00:54:35,605 --> 00:54:36,773
It's so exciting

945
00:54:38,357 --> 00:54:40,777
to be able to introduce you as my wife
to everyone.

946
00:54:41,402 --> 00:54:43,070
I'm not good at being a wife.

947
00:54:43,279 --> 00:54:45,323
I'm just here to congratulate you, too.

948
00:54:45,823 --> 00:54:47,158
I know.

949
00:54:47,700 --> 00:54:49,827
- That was why I invited you.
- Hmm?

950
00:54:49,994 --> 00:54:52,371
I saw how good you were at applauding

951
00:54:53,456 --> 00:54:55,541
at that awards ceremony.

952
00:54:57,418 --> 00:55:01,047
Next, we'll award Dr. Shin
with an appreciation plaque

953
00:55:01,130 --> 00:55:03,800
and hear his inauguration speech
as the new Director.

954
00:55:14,435 --> 00:55:16,062
Dear distinguished colleagues

955
00:55:16,395 --> 00:55:20,900
I will bear my position as the Director
of HKUH with great weight.

956
00:55:21,275 --> 00:55:25,947
Moreover, I'll sacrifice myself
to make HKUK a leader of medicine.

957
00:55:26,113 --> 00:55:28,616
All of you have made great contribution

958
00:55:28,699 --> 00:55:33,788
to build
the hospital's reputation and value.

959
00:55:34,038 --> 00:55:40,086
I'll do my best as the Director
to keep up the reputation and value.

960
00:55:41,128 --> 00:55:42,213
Thank you.

961
00:55:51,681 --> 00:55:53,140
One, two, three.

962
00:55:54,100 --> 00:55:55,184
One more.

963
00:55:55,351 --> 00:55:56,769
One, two, three.

964
00:55:59,564 --> 00:56:01,524
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

965
00:56:05,570 --> 00:56:07,864
You're even more beautiful in person!

966
00:56:07,989 --> 00:56:08,990
Hello.

967
00:56:09,073 --> 00:56:11,784
I hear you were his patient,
and that was how you met.

968
00:56:11,868 --> 00:56:13,661
And you traveled to Cannes together.

969
00:56:13,870 --> 00:56:15,454
It was a coincidence.

970
00:56:16,080 --> 00:56:19,917
We're doctors, too.
How come we don't meet celebrities?

971
00:56:20,001 --> 00:56:21,669
He's just another doctor, like you.

972
00:56:21,752 --> 00:56:25,298
Did you two get close in Cannes?

973
00:56:25,381 --> 00:56:27,133
Well, you know...

974
00:56:28,050 --> 00:56:29,302
See you around.

975
00:56:29,385 --> 00:56:31,596
Please help Dr. Shin
with his new position.

976
00:56:31,804 --> 00:56:32,847
Thank you.

977
00:56:39,061 --> 00:56:42,899
So, they didn't meet at the hospital,
but it was still an affair.

978
00:56:43,149 --> 00:56:46,777
It's even worse, consdering how his wife
was almost dying.

979
00:56:47,320 --> 00:56:48,738
Who doesn't know about him

980
00:56:48,821 --> 00:56:52,241
ignoring calls from the hospital
and his son when he went to France?

981
00:56:52,450 --> 00:56:53,618
I know, right?

982
00:56:55,453 --> 00:56:57,538
How can someone be so cruel?

983
00:56:57,830 --> 00:56:59,415
You really can't trust anyone, huh?

984
00:57:32,365 --> 00:57:33,449
Hello.

985
00:57:33,532 --> 00:57:34,742
Ui-yeong!

986
00:57:35,284 --> 00:57:36,827
- Oh, hello.
- Hi.

987
00:57:37,411 --> 00:57:40,331
You look great today.

988
00:57:41,207 --> 00:57:42,833
Really? Thanks.

989
00:57:42,917 --> 00:57:47,088
I know you've gone
on a lot of blind dates lately.

990
00:57:48,005 --> 00:57:49,548
- Yeah.
- But as you know

991
00:57:49,632 --> 00:57:53,844
blind dates are good experience,
even if things don't work out.

992
00:57:53,928 --> 00:57:56,263
And sometimes, you get lucky
and find a good one.

993
00:57:56,931 --> 00:57:58,307
- I guess so.
- Yeah.

994
00:57:58,391 --> 00:58:02,353
I booked a table at Harrod in Cheongdam.
Take the card.

995
00:58:03,229 --> 00:58:07,233
Order whatever you want with it, okay?

996
00:58:07,984 --> 00:58:10,444
So, Mr. Choi's youngest son is coming?

997
00:58:10,528 --> 00:58:12,238
And he butchers tiger cattles?

998
00:58:12,321 --> 00:58:14,865
He should be around your age,
considering Mr. Choi's age.

999
00:58:15,074 --> 00:58:17,034
He basically runs a moo-d-sized company

1000
00:58:17,118 --> 00:58:20,705
with all those expensive cows
running around in that big farm.

1001
00:58:21,956 --> 00:58:23,040
So funny.

1002
00:58:24,625 --> 00:58:26,502
- Anyway, good luck.
- Sure.

1003
00:58:28,629 --> 00:58:29,672
Moo-d-sized...

1004
00:58:40,391 --> 00:58:41,434
Na-ri.

1005
00:58:42,560 --> 00:58:43,561
Here.

1006
00:58:44,145 --> 00:58:45,146
What is it?

1007
00:58:45,229 --> 00:58:48,232
All the docs for today's meeting.

1008
00:58:49,900 --> 00:58:54,155
I'll do my best not to ruin
all the hard work you put in

1009
00:58:54,280 --> 00:58:57,867
and make sure the meeting goes well.

1010
00:59:02,038 --> 00:59:03,080
Okay.

1011
00:59:17,553 --> 00:59:22,975
Mr. Oh, can I see you at the cafe
by the hotel after work?

1012
00:59:27,813 --> 00:59:29,190
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

1013
00:59:34,070 --> 00:59:36,906
What did you want to talk about?

1014
00:59:42,036 --> 00:59:43,204
I'm so mad.

1015
00:59:44,538 --> 00:59:46,290
- Hmm?
- I know Ui-yeong is good.

1016
00:59:46,373 --> 00:59:47,458
She motivates me, too.

1017
00:59:47,541 --> 00:59:50,169
But you went too far with this project!

1018
00:59:50,377 --> 00:59:53,297
You know I worked late nights
for days for this!

1019
00:59:53,380 --> 00:59:56,133
I know. I really do. Who doesn't?

1020
00:59:56,217 --> 00:59:57,802
I know you worked hard on it.

1021
00:59:57,885 --> 00:59:59,303
Why did you do this, then?

1022
01:00:00,221 --> 01:00:02,181
I know I can do well.

1023
01:00:02,264 --> 01:00:03,808
I can go to the meeting right now...

1024
01:00:03,891 --> 01:00:05,768
Hey! Stop it.

1025
01:00:05,976 --> 01:00:08,562
A no is a no! Don't be like that.

1026
01:00:08,896 --> 01:00:13,400
Stay still if you don't want to ruin it,
okay?

1027
01:00:13,484 --> 01:00:16,237
Why? At least tell me why!

1028
01:00:16,320 --> 01:00:18,531
You have...

1029
01:00:20,032 --> 01:00:21,325
a family!

1030
01:00:21,867 --> 01:00:23,828
Whatever! I'm going home.

1031
01:00:24,495 --> 01:00:26,330
- Whatever.
- Myeong-un!

1032
01:00:35,297 --> 01:00:37,216
The more I think about it,
the worse it gets.

1033
01:00:38,467 --> 01:00:40,970
Sure, I've skipped a few site visits

1034
01:00:41,053 --> 01:00:43,347
by using my family and in-laws
as an excuse.

1035
01:00:43,430 --> 01:00:46,308
But I've worked here for long enough
to do that.

1036
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:51,647
How can he throw me out of a project
just for that?

1037
01:00:52,439 --> 01:00:53,941
Because I have a family?

1038
01:00:54,441 --> 01:00:56,152
How does that make any sense?

1039
01:00:58,946 --> 01:01:02,616
It's so odd for him to stop you
from trying to work harder.

1040
01:01:03,284 --> 01:01:04,451
When's the meeting?

1041
01:01:07,163 --> 01:01:08,747
I'm sure she's on her way now.

1042
01:01:09,248 --> 01:01:12,960
They're meeting at Harrod
in Cheongdam or something.

1043
01:01:14,170 --> 01:01:15,921
People have work meetings at such places?

1044
01:01:16,005 --> 01:01:17,548
Why? Do you know the place?

1045
01:01:17,631 --> 01:01:19,341
Yeah, I used to work there.

1046
01:01:20,467 --> 01:01:23,179
It's not really a business meeting vibe.

1047
01:01:23,888 --> 01:01:26,140
It's a famous spot in the area
for blind dates.

1048
01:01:28,893 --> 01:01:29,977
Hold up.

1049
01:01:31,687 --> 01:01:35,149
Mr. Choi's son is coming to the meeting.

1050
01:01:38,944 --> 01:01:42,615
I can't go as a married woman... No way.

1051
01:01:43,949 --> 01:01:45,159
- A blind date?
- A blind date?

1052
01:01:51,916 --> 01:01:54,501
Are you Ms. Lee Ui-yeong?

1053
01:01:54,627 --> 01:01:56,962
Are you Mr. Choi's youngest son?

1054
01:01:57,046 --> 01:01:58,881
- Yeah.
- Hello.

1055
01:01:59,381 --> 01:02:01,592
I'm Lee Ui-yeong from Purchasing
at The Hills Hotel.

1056
01:02:01,675 --> 01:02:04,803
Oh, a business card.

1057
01:02:06,889 --> 01:02:08,724
- I'm Choi U-jun.
- I see.

1058
01:02:09,934 --> 01:02:13,145
The traffic on the way was terrible!

1059
01:02:13,729 --> 01:02:15,439
It was a long drive, right?

1060
01:02:15,522 --> 01:02:16,774
It's fine.

1061
01:02:16,857 --> 01:02:17,942
Should we head in?

1062
01:02:18,025 --> 01:02:19,026
- Oh, sure.
- Okay.

1063
01:02:23,864 --> 01:02:25,658
This is perfect. I was getting hungry.

1064
01:02:27,159 --> 01:02:28,786
Would you like to have dinner?

1065
01:02:29,036 --> 01:02:30,746
Yeah, a dinner.

1066
01:02:30,829 --> 01:02:31,872
Okay.

1067
01:02:34,250 --> 01:02:36,585
The menu's hard to read.

1068
01:02:36,710 --> 01:02:40,339
Please order some good meat for me.

1069
01:02:40,422 --> 01:02:41,924
Oh, sure. Meat.

1070
01:02:44,218 --> 01:02:45,219
Excuse me.

1071
01:02:48,681 --> 01:02:52,059
We'll take two steaks, please.

1072
01:02:52,142 --> 01:02:54,395
Okay, how would you like them cooked?

1073
01:02:54,478 --> 01:02:58,607
If it's fresh, medium-rare.
If not, medium.

1074
01:02:59,692 --> 01:03:02,611
Oh, and wine! You want wine?
We'll take two.

1075
01:03:02,987 --> 01:03:05,281
Okay, we'll get them ready soon.

1076
01:03:05,447 --> 01:03:06,490
Thank you.

1077
01:03:12,997 --> 01:03:14,373
- What should we do?
- The device you’re trying to reach...

1078
01:03:14,456 --> 01:03:16,667
I can't reach Mr. Oh or Ui-yeong.

1079
01:03:22,840 --> 01:03:23,882
Hello?

1080
01:03:25,509 --> 01:03:26,552
Hey, honey.

1081
01:03:27,261 --> 01:03:28,304
Are you off now?

1082
01:03:29,263 --> 01:03:31,557
Yeah, I'll be home soon. Bye.

1083
01:03:33,559 --> 01:03:36,061
I'd better get going.

1084
01:03:36,145 --> 01:03:38,480
I'll keep calling her when I get home.

1085
01:03:38,564 --> 01:03:40,316
- She'll pick up eventually.
- Okay.

1086
01:03:40,524 --> 01:03:41,734
My gosh.

1087
01:03:42,109 --> 01:03:44,486
- Hello.
- Hello.

1088
01:03:45,112 --> 01:03:47,781
- Is everything good?
- Actually, something urgent came up.

1089
01:03:47,948 --> 01:03:49,533
Can I go home a bit early?

1090
01:03:49,616 --> 01:03:51,076
Huh? Oh, sure.

1091
01:03:51,160 --> 01:03:52,578
- Thank you.
- Okay.

1092
01:04:00,711 --> 01:04:02,046
My father said

1093
01:04:02,755 --> 01:04:06,300
your eyes resembled
our cows' eyes at the farm.

1094
01:04:07,009 --> 01:04:08,093
He was right.

1095
01:04:09,136 --> 01:04:14,475
Everyone fights over those cows
with bright eyes at the market.

1096
01:04:14,725 --> 01:04:17,770
Funny how you're still single, huh?

1097
01:04:19,855 --> 01:04:20,898
You think so?

1098
01:04:22,733 --> 01:04:26,445
Oh, this is the proposal from the hotel.

1099
01:04:26,612 --> 01:04:27,654
Oh.

1100
01:04:28,280 --> 01:04:29,656
Do I read it now?

1101
01:04:31,367 --> 01:04:33,035
ARK OF TASTE SELECTION:
PROPOSAL FOR TIGER CATTLE BEEF SET

1102
01:04:33,118 --> 01:04:34,286
That's the first draft.

1103
01:04:34,370 --> 01:04:37,915
Idae Farm can decide
on what's in the set and the quantities.

1104
01:04:41,251 --> 01:04:44,004
Oh, here comes our food!
Why don't we eat first?

1105
01:04:44,088 --> 01:04:45,130
Sure.

1106
01:04:45,964 --> 01:04:47,007
Thank you.

1107
01:04:47,674 --> 01:04:48,759
This looks great!

1108
01:04:55,140 --> 01:04:56,892
Is this raw or something?

1109
01:04:56,975 --> 01:04:58,185
I can crush you.

1110
01:04:58,268 --> 01:05:01,814
I bet you didn't know
I was a butcher, huh?

1111
01:05:03,941 --> 01:05:05,818
I guess it's my time to shine.

1112
01:05:09,279 --> 01:05:10,614
Sir...

1113
01:05:11,532 --> 01:05:13,742
You have to use this knife.

1114
01:05:15,661 --> 01:05:16,787
Oh!

1115
01:05:20,457 --> 01:05:25,003
I must look like such a country bumpkin
in your eyes, huh?

1116
01:05:25,087 --> 01:05:26,505
Oh, not at all.

1117
01:05:26,713 --> 01:05:30,551
I also use scissors to eat meat at home.

1118
01:05:31,510 --> 01:05:33,429
You're a lot more chill than you seem!

1119
01:05:34,555 --> 01:05:36,056
Well, nice to meet you.

1120
01:05:47,067 --> 01:05:49,445
One more glass!

1121
01:05:49,653 --> 01:05:53,949
Hey! Don't be stingy.
Fill the glass to the rim, alright?

1122
01:05:59,288 --> 01:06:00,456
Okay.

1123
01:06:10,215 --> 01:06:11,216
Hey!

1124
01:06:16,555 --> 01:06:18,891
Man, I'm getting hot!

1125
01:06:38,410 --> 01:06:39,745
If I drink more

1126
01:06:40,287 --> 01:06:41,830
we won't be able to talk business

1127
01:06:42,039 --> 01:06:43,999
- and I won't even manage to get home.
- Hey...

1128
01:06:45,792 --> 01:06:47,085
Why are you so far away?

1129
01:06:47,920 --> 01:06:51,173
We, butchers

1130
01:06:51,256 --> 01:06:55,636
always end up arm wrestling
in the middle of our shifts!

1131
01:06:55,719 --> 01:06:58,722
Our forearms are so strong
that we can't stop ourselves.

1132
01:06:58,805 --> 01:06:59,973
Touch it.

1133
01:07:00,057 --> 01:07:01,350
What? No, thanks.

1134
01:07:01,433 --> 01:07:03,393
It's fine, I'm older! Go ahead.

1135
01:07:03,477 --> 01:07:05,896
I can tell by the look of it.

1136
01:07:05,979 --> 01:07:08,273
Don't be so shy.

1137
01:07:08,357 --> 01:07:10,817
I guess you haven't dated many men.

1138
01:07:10,901 --> 01:07:12,903
You're old enough to know everything.

1139
01:07:12,986 --> 01:07:14,947
It's not fun

1140
01:07:15,030 --> 01:07:17,574
when a woman keeps acting so innocent.

1141
01:07:17,991 --> 01:07:20,869
So, how many men have you dated?

1142
01:07:21,245 --> 01:07:22,913
Three? Four?

1143
01:07:24,831 --> 01:07:27,459
He's the worst of the worst.

1144
01:07:28,001 --> 01:07:29,962
Mr. Choi

1145
01:07:30,045 --> 01:07:31,046
Yeah?

1146
01:07:31,672 --> 01:07:33,882
this is a business meeting.

1147
01:07:34,508 --> 01:07:36,468
- Huh?
- Please refrain from asking

1148
01:07:36,552 --> 01:07:37,970
unrelated questions.

1149
01:07:42,266 --> 01:07:45,477
Why do you keep talking about work
all evening?

1150
01:07:45,727 --> 01:07:49,189
Just be good to me, go along with me

1151
01:07:49,273 --> 01:07:53,110
and all that business talk will go well!

1152
01:07:53,277 --> 01:07:56,154
Isn't that why you've been so nice to me
all evening?

1153
01:07:56,238 --> 01:07:58,865
Let's just be honest, okay?

1154
01:07:58,949 --> 01:08:02,035
To be honest, the only reason
I'm being cordial is

1155
01:08:02,119 --> 01:08:05,539
that I want to convince you
to trust and respect the hotel.

1156
01:08:06,582 --> 01:08:09,293
I have no interest
in building a personal relationship.

1157
01:08:10,127 --> 01:08:11,878
- Huh?
- So, Mr. Choi

1158
01:08:11,962 --> 01:08:16,133
please get back to considering
whether the deal can be profitable to you.

1159
01:08:16,300 --> 01:08:17,384
Instead of me.

1160
01:08:18,093 --> 01:08:21,305
You can read our proposal.
I need to call my supervisor.

1161
01:08:21,680 --> 01:08:22,973
Hold on.

1162
01:08:27,311 --> 01:08:28,770
That's condescending of you.

1163
01:08:29,563 --> 01:08:30,647
Sit down.

1164
01:08:30,897 --> 01:08:32,357
Sit down right now!

1165
01:08:37,404 --> 01:08:39,448
You've had too much to drink.

1166
01:08:40,282 --> 01:08:42,576
Let's end the meeting here.

1167
01:08:43,201 --> 01:08:44,494
I'll call you another time.

1168
01:08:45,871 --> 01:08:47,414
Where the hell are you going?

1169
01:08:47,497 --> 01:08:49,541
That hurts! Let go!

1170
01:08:49,625 --> 01:08:50,917
You think you can just leave?

1171
01:08:51,001 --> 01:08:52,961
- Let go! It hurts!
- No!

1172
01:08:58,300 --> 01:08:59,801
Tae-seop!

1173
01:09:00,427 --> 01:09:01,845
Who the hell are you?

1174
01:09:01,928 --> 01:09:04,264
Me? Her boyfriend.

1175
01:09:24,785 --> 01:09:27,579
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

1176
01:09:33,502 --> 01:09:36,171
CONGRATULATIONS,
YOU FINALLY HAVE A GIRLFRIEND

1177
01:09:48,433 --> 01:09:51,770
I REALLY LIKE YOU

1178
01:09:52,688 --> 01:09:55,565
TOO DANGEROUS

1179
01:10:01,029 --> 01:10:03,699
How did you know to come here?

1180
01:10:04,950 --> 01:10:07,160
Until the Disciplinary Committee decides
what to do with Mr. Oh...

1181
01:10:08,995 --> 01:10:10,330
There's nothing to do.

1182
01:10:10,414 --> 01:10:12,874
You know things you've been putting off
because you've been busy.

1183
01:10:12,958 --> 01:10:14,334
Do those, one by one.

1184
01:10:15,502 --> 01:10:16,503
It's for you.

1185
01:10:17,170 --> 01:10:19,381
I'm getting a divorce.

1186
01:10:20,006 --> 01:10:21,007
What?

1187
01:10:21,091 --> 01:10:23,176
You have to get back to work soon

1188
01:10:23,260 --> 01:10:25,470
so it'll be nice to go on a trip,
even if it's short.

1189
01:10:29,141 --> 01:10:30,183
Dad!

1190
01:10:30,267 --> 01:10:31,518
Your father?

1191
01:10:37,149 --> 01:10:39,151
Subtitles by: Min-sun Kim
